reader /ˈriːdə/

(readers) 

1. N-COUNT The readers of a newspaper, magazine, or book are the people who read it. 读者 

例： These texts give the reader an insight into the Chinese mind. 这些文章让读者对中国式的思维有了深入了解。 

例： The paper's success is simple: we give our readers what they want. 本报的成功很简单：我们给读者他们想要的东西。 

2. N-COUNT A reader is a person who reads, especially one who reads for pleasure. 读书的人 (尤指为获得乐趣) 

例： Thanks to that job I became an avid reader. 多亏那项工作我成了一个爱读书的人。

